  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Purchaser",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Conduct comprehensive research and analysis on products, vendors, and services to secure optimal deals. Lead contract negotiations and collaborate with cross-functional teams to ensure timely delivery and inventory management. Drive vendor networking and product inspection to maintain quality standards and support informed purchasing decisions.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Conduct detailed research on potential products, vendors, and services to compare price and quality, ensuring cost-effective procurement decisions</li><li>Lead negotiations with vendors and clients to secure favorable contract terms that align with business objectives</li><li>Coordinate with delivery and warehouse teams to guarantee timely receipt of goods and smooth logistics operations</li><li>Monitor inventory levels and generate purchase orders to maintain optimal stock availability</li><li>Represent the company at industry events, shows, and exhibitions to build vendor relationships and identify innovative products</li><li>Inspect delivered products for quality and compliance, reporting discrepancies promptly to mitigate risks</li><li>Maintain accurate and up-to-date records of all purchased products for transparency and audit purposes</li><li>Prepare detailed reports on purchasing activities and perform cost analyses to inform strategic sourcing decisions</li><li>Actively participate in meetings with staff and stakeholders to contribute insights and align purchasing strategies with organizational goals</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Practical experience using purchasing software to manage procurement processes effectively</li><li>Strong analytical skills to evaluate vendor proposals and purchasing data for informed decision-making</li><li>Proficient research and networking skills to identify and engage with reliable vendors and market opportunities</li><li>Excellent written, verbal, and interpersonal communication skills to negotiate contracts and collaborate across teams</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Retail industry experience or similar background to understand market dynamics and customer needs</li><li>Bachelor of Science degree in business administration or a related field to support business acumen and operational understanding</li></ul>",
